# Local Environment Variables - ALTERNATIVE TO SECRETS BROKER
# 
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT: This is an EXAMPLE template file.
# To use local environment variables instead of the secrets broker, you MUST:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local in your project root
# 2. Modify the variables to match your project's needs
# 3. Remove any example variables you don't need
#
# This file provides local defaults for environment variables, bypassing the need
# for the secrets broker system. Useful when:
# - Running on OS that can't run the broker
# - Wanting simple local development setup
# - Testing without external credential sources
#
# FORMAT:
# - One variable per line: VARIABLE_NAME=value
# - No spaces around the = sign
# - Values are treated as literal strings
# - Use quotes for values with spaces: VARIABLE="value with spaces"
#
# EXAMPLES (modify these for your project):

# Database connection string for local development
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://localhost:5432/myapp_dev"

# API key for local testing (use test keys, never real production keys)
PAYMENT_API_KEY="sk_test_1234567890abcdef"

# AWS credentials for local development (use test account)
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE"
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY="wJalrXUtnFEMI/K7MDENG/bPxRfiCYEXAMPLEKEY"

# GitHub token for local development (use personal access token)
GITHUB_TOKEN="ghp_1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef12345678"

# Path to original home directory (before container mapping)
ORIGINAL_HOME="/home/username"

# Local development server port
SERVER_PORT="3000"

# Debug mode for local development
DEBUG="true"

# USAGE:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local in your project root
# 2. Edit the values to match your local development environment
# 3. Remove any variables you don't need
# 4. The secrets client will use these values instead of requesting from broker
#
# SECURITY:
# - This file is in .gitignore and will NOT be committed to git
# - Use test/development values, never production secrets
# - Each developer maintains their own .env.local file
# - This provides a simple alternative to the secrets broker system
#
# PRIORITY ORDER:
# 1. .env.requirements (variable definitions and descriptions)
# 2. .env.local (local default values - overrides requirements defaults)
# 3. Secrets broker (for any variables still missing values)
